{{Infobox Treaty |name =Hague Protection of Adults Convention |long_name = Convention of 13 January 2000 on the International Protection of Adults |image =ProtectionOfAdultsConvention.svg |image_width =260 |caption ={{legend|#00aaee|Party}} {{legend|#ffff33|Signatory that did not ratify}} |type = |date_drafted = |date_signed = 13 January 2000 |location_signed = [[The Hague]], The Netherlands |date_sealed = |date_effective = 1 January 2009 |condition_effective = Ratification by 3 states<ref name=HCCHtext/> |date_expiration = |signatories = 17<ref name=parties/> |parties = 10<ref name=parties/> |depositor = [[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Netherlands)]]<ref name=HCCHtext/> |language = |languages = English and French<ref name=HCCHtext/> |wikisource = }} The '''Hague Protection of Adults Convention''', formally the '''Convention on the International Protection of Adults''' is convention concluded by the [[Hague Conference on Private International Law]] in 2000.<ref name=HCCHtext>{{cite web|url=https://www.hcch.net/en/instruments/conventions/full-text/?cid=71|title=35: Convention of 13 January 2000 on the International Protection of Adults|accessdate=8 February 2017|publisher=HCCH}}</ref> The convention entered into force in 2009 and currently applies in nine states.<ref name=parties>{{cite web|url=https://verdragenbank.overheid.nl/en/Verdrag/Details/009250|title=Convention on the international protection of adults, Treaty data|accessdate=8 February 2017|work=Treaty Database of the Netherlands}}</ref> The convention is aimed at the protection of [[Vulnerable adult]]s, persons who are "by reason of an impairment or insufficiency of their personal faculties, are not in a position to protect their interests". The convention *determines which courts have [[jurisdiction]] to take protection measures *determines [[applicable law|which law]] is to be applied in the circumstances; and who may be a vulnerable person *establishes a system of central authorities which should cooperate, locate vulnerable adults and give information on the status of vulnerable persons to other authorities
==Parties== As of November 2017, the convention applies in 9 states. Furthermore, the convention will enter into force for Latvia in 2018.
